Kebbi Governor Abubakar Bagudu has commiserated with residents of Kamba town over the fire incident which occurred on Saturday night at Kamba central market. The Governor has also directed the immediate reconstruction of shops and stalls affected by the fire outbreak at Kamba . He also ordered the immediate provision of relief assistance to the victims.  Bagudu, represented by the Deputy Governor Samaâ€™ila Yombe Dabai, gave the directive when he led a powerful government delegation to Kamba on Sunday to sympathise with the victims.   NRC suspends 8 am train ride     Zamfara schools resume Jan. 17     Brymo lashes Nigerians living abroad   - Advertisement - He expressed sympathies to the people of Kamba and Dandi Local Government on the tragic incident. He assured that the state government would bring immediate succor to those affected to recoup losses and restart their businesses as usual. The Deputy Governor accompanied by top government officials inspected the burnt stalls and addressed the marketers at the scene of the inferno.